>>> print (hello) ====> Make sure always use double quotes to print a string else python consider it as a parameter and throw's error if the parameter is not defined
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "<pyshell#0>", line 1, in <module>
    print (hello)
NameError: name 'hello' is not defined
>>> print ("Hello")
Hello
>>> hello=60 ====> parameter defined here.
>>> print (hello)
60
